6721 /******************************************************************************/
6722 /* For a painless codes migration between the STM32F0xx device product */
6723 /* lines, the aliases defined below are put in place to overcome the */
6724 /* differences in the interrupt handlers and IRQn definitions. */
6725 /* No need to update developed interrupt code when moving across */
6726 /* product lines within the same STM32F0 Family */
6727 /******************************************************************************/
6728 
6729 /* Aliases for __IRQn */

6731 #define DMA1_Ch1_IRQn DMA1_Channel1_IRQn
6732 #define DMA1_Ch2_3_DMA2_Ch1_2_IRQn DMA1_Channel2_3_IRQn
6733 #define DMA1_Channel4_5_6_7_IRQn DMA1_Channel4_5_IRQn
6734 #define DMA1_Ch4_7_DMA2_Ch3_5_IRQn DMA1_Channel4_5_IRQn
6735 #define PVD_VDDIO2_IRQn PVD_IRQn
6736 #define VDDIO2_IRQn PVD_IRQn
6737 #define RCC_CRS_IRQn RCC_IRQn
6738 #define TIM6_IRQn TIM6_DAC_IRQn
6739 
6740 
6741 /* Aliases for __IRQHandler */
6742 #define ADC1_IRQHandler ADC1_COMP_IRQHandler
6743 #define DMA1_Ch1_IRQHandler DMA1_Channel1_IRQHandler
6744 #define DMA1_Ch2_3_DMA2_Ch1_2_IRQHandler DMA1_Channel2_3_IRQHandler
6745 #define DMA1_Channel4_5_6_7_IRQHandler DMA1_Channel4_5_IRQHandler
6746 #define DMA1_Ch4_7_DMA2_Ch3_5_IRQHandler DMA1_Channel4_5_IRQHandler
6747 #define PVD_VDDIO2_IRQHandler PVD_IRQHandler
6748 #define VDDIO2_IRQHandler PVD_IRQHandler
